|WKB                           THE QUEST SYSTEM
|CKB=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

|YKODarkWind features a quest system that gives you objectives to
complete for experience and gold rewards. Quests range from simple
tasks like slaying a few monsters to multi-step adventures involving
item retrieval, rescues, and escorts.

|WKBGetting Started:|XX0

|YKO  1. Find the waysteward beside an area's wayshard or entrance.
  2. A bright yellow |YKB[?] |YKOmeans the steward has work available.
  3. Use |YKBengage waysteward |YKOto review and accept a quest.
  4. Complete its objectives; a bright yellow |YKB[!] |YKOthen appears.
  5. Engage the same area's waysteward to turn in the quest and collect rewards.

|WKBKey Concepts:|XX0

|YKO  You may accept multiple quests. All accepted quests track progress
  automatically, so you do not need to choose an active quest.

  Each quest has one or more |WKBobjectives|YKO. These tell you what to
  do - kill certain creatures, find specific items, rescue someone,
  or escort an NPC to safety. Use |YKBqstatus |YKOto check your progress.

